      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_jproteome_0c00866__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "By using the read Index() function a data.frame that indexes all scans found in a raw fi le is returned... For regression, we now extract the RTs at the maximum of the intensity traces stored in the rawrr Chromatogram object and fi t a linear model of the form rt = a + b \u00b7 score... Figure 6 shows a visual inspection by plotting observed RTs as a function of iRT score together with the fi tted model regression line. The corresponding R-squared indicates that the RTs behave highly linear.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly demonstrates iRT regression with R-squared evaluation of RT linearity.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Does the linear regression model fitted to iRT peptide retention times (rtFittedAPEX ~ iRTscore) demonstrate highly linear RT behavior as indicated by R-squared value?",
