    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_jproteome_0c00866__task_003/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In total, the API provides 82 data items for this particular scan covering ion optics settings, mass calibration, and other diagnostic data... Individual scans or scan collections (sets) can be read by the function read Spectrum() which returns a rawrr Spectrum object or rawrr Spectrum Set.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper states 82 data items for scan 9594, not 119. The card claims 119 items but the paper explicitly states 'In total, the API provides 82 data items for this particular scan'. The object type and content categories (m/z, intensity, resolving power, AGC, injection time) are correct.",
