      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "an Orbitrap detector including lock mass correction and using a transient of 64 ms (equal to a resolving power of 30 000 at 200 m/z) and an AGC target of 1 \u00d7 10^5 elementary charges... it becomes apparent that the C-trap managed to collect the defined 100 000 charges within 2.8 ms... Figure 2 shows that all y-ion signals are several ten or even hundred folds above the noise estimate",
      "asbval:note": "All three validation metrics are explicitly confirmed in the paper for scan 9594.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
