      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-precursor-identification/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "By applying linear regression, one can convert observed peptide retention times (RTs) into dimensionless scores termed iRT values and vice versa. This can be used for retention time calibration/prediction.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly demonstrates RT calibration via iRT regression modeling.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-precursor-identification",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "establish retention time calibration curves",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:30.615372+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-precursor-identification/011",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The initial step of iRT regression is to estimate the empirical RTs of a peptide set with known iRT scores. In the simplest case, this is achieved by computing an extracted ion chromatogram (XIC) for iRT peptide precursors, provided they were spiked into the sample matrix prior to data acquisition.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses iRT peptides with known reference scores as the standard peptide set.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-precursor-identification",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "iRT peptides as known reference standards",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:30.615372+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our novel package rawrr now provides complete, OS-independent access to all spectral data logged in Thermo Fisher Scientific raw files... The API provides 82 data items for this particular scan covering ion optics settings, mass calibration, and other diagnostic data... Diagnostic information related to the Orbitrap's advanced gain control (AGC) system, it becomes apparent that the C-trap managed to collect the defined 100 000 charges within 2.8 ms",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly demonstrates extraction of spectral metadata, AGC charge collection metrics, and scan-level performance diagnostics from Orbitrap raw files.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Extract and interpret spectral metadata and ion trap instrumentation parameters from Thermo Orbitrap raw files to characterize acquisition conditions, charge collection, and scan-level performance metrics.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:49.468965+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our novel package rawrr now provides complete, OS-independent access to all spectral data logged in Thermo Fisher Scientific raw files... R functions requesting access to data stored in binary raw files (reader family functions listed in Table 1) invoke compiled C# wrapper methods using a system call... The respective function is called readFileHeader() and returns a simple R object of type list... Individual scans or scan collections (sets) can be read by the function readSpectrum()... The code chunk below demonstrates how the function readChromatogram() is called on the R command line to return a rawrr Chromatogram Set object",
      "asbval:note": "All named functions (readFileHeader, readSpectrum, readIndex, readChromatogram) are explicitly documented in the paper with their roles and return types.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "rawrr: R package wrapping RawFileReader .NET assembly; provides readFileHeader(), readSpectrum(), readIndex(), readChromatogram() functions for direct access to Orbitrap binary data",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:49.468965+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "rawrr utilizes a vendor-provided API named Raw File Reader to access spectral data logged in proprietary Thermo Fisher Scientific raw files... Calling a wrapper method typically results in the execution of methods defined in the Raw File Reader dynamic link library provided by Thermo Fisher Scientific... Running rawrr.exe requires the Mono environment on non-Microsoft operating systems. Mono is a cross platform, open source .NET framework. On Microsoft Windows the Microsoft.NET framework is typically already installed and sufficient.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms RawFileReader is the vendor-provided API, invoked via C# wrappers, and supports cross-platform execution (Windows, Linux via Mono, macOS).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "RawFileReader: .NET assembly (ThermoFisher.CommonCore.RawFileReader) invoked via C# wrapper methods by rawrr; reads binary Orbitrap data on Windows, Linux, macOS",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:49.468965+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our R package rawDiag (J. Proteome Res. 2018, 17 (8), 2908\u20132914) has provided the proof-of-principle how access to mass spectrometry raw files can be realized by wrapping a vendor-provided advanced programming interface (API) for the purpose of metadata analysis and visualization... Its codebase evolved from our previous R package rawDiag.",
      "asbval:note": "rawDiag is confirmed as a predecessor package for metadata analysis and visualization; rawrr evolved from it. Role as complementary tool for diagnostics is supported by the paper's framing.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "rawDiag: R package for LC-MS method optimization and raw file diagnostics; complements rawrr for visualization and interpretation of instrument performance",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:49.468965+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In case you prefer to compile `rawrr.exe` from C# source code, please install the .NET 8.0",
      "asbval:note": "Paper mentions .NET 8.0 in context of compilation from source, but does not explicitly state it is required for runtime execution. Paper states 'On Microsoft Windows the Microsoft.NET framework is typically already installed and sufficient' and 'Running rawrr.exe requires the Mono environment on non-Microsoft operating systems.' The specific version requirement (8.0) is mentioned only for compilation, not runtime verification. Partial support: .NET runtime is required, but the paper does not confirm 8.0 is the minimum/required version for execution.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": ".NET 8.0 runtime: Execution environment required for RawFileReader .NET assemblies; must be installed and verified before rawrr operation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:49.468965+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We use a complete LC-MS run recorded on a Q Exactive HF Orbitrap by parallel reaction monitoring (PRM)... The Orbitrap detector has been a tremendous success story in MS, since it offers HRAM data on a time scale that is compatible with chromatographic analysis (LC-MS) and is therefore heavily used in bottom-up proteomics... Diagnostic information related to the Orbitrap's advanced gain control (AGC) system, it becomes apparent that the C-trap managed to collect the defined 100 000 charges within 2.8 ms, corresponding to only \u223c 5% of the maximum injection time of 55 ms... By using the readIndex() function a data.frame that indexes all scans found in a raw file is returned. When subsetting it for our scan type of interest it becomes clear that the example data was recorded using parallel reaction monitoring (PRM)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates all use cases mentioned: Q Exactive HF instrument, C-trap charge collection metrics, injection time utilization, scan type classification (PRM), and isolation parameters.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have a Thermo Scientific .raw file from an Orbitrap instrument (e.g., Q Exactive HF) and need to understand or verify acquisition-time instrument behavior: charge collection in the C-trap, injection time utilization, scan type classification, mass range configuration, or",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:49.468965+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "rawrr now provides complete, OS-independent access to all spectral data logged in Thermo Fisher Scientific raw files... However, analyzing Orbitrap data in R has so far only been possible after raw data conversion to exchange formats like mz(X)ML. Unfortunately, conversion is accompanied by a loss of Orbitrap-specific information.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms rawrr is specific to Thermo Fisher Scientific raw files and that conversion to mzML/mzXML is an alternative (but lossy) approach, implying rawrr does not natively support those formats.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "orbitrap-spectrum-acquisition-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input is not a Thermo .raw file (e.g., mzML, mzXML, Bruker, or Waters formats) \u2014 rawrr is instrument-vendor specific.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:39:49.468965+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
