    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/r-internal-function-invocation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes the rawrr package architecture (two-layer R/C# implementation, vendor API wrapping, reader functions) but does not mention or demonstrate the use of ::: (triple-colon) operators to invoke unexported internal functions, nor does it reference functions like .rawrrAssembly() or .getRawrrAssemblyVersion(). The paper focuses on exported reader functions (readFileHeader, readSpectrum, readChromatogram, readIndex) and does not discuss internal metadata retrieval via ::: syntax.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "r-internal-function-invocation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Invoke unexported R package internal functions (prefixed with :::) to access low-level assembly dispatch and configuration metadata without requiring raw data file inputs.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:40:44.210269+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/r-internal-function-invocation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our implementation consists of two language layers, the top R layer and the hidden C # layer. Specifically, R functions requesting access to data stored in binary raw files (reader family functions listed in Table 1) invoke compiled C # wrapper methods using a system call.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms the two-layer R/C# architecture and mentions that R functions invoke C# wrapper methods, but does not describe or demonstrate any mechanism for querying assembly paths or version information via internal functions. The paper does not mention .NET assembly path retrieval or version querying as a capability.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "r-internal-function-invocation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill enables direct querying of bundled .NET assembly paths and version information in the rawrr package's two-layer R/C# architecture.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:40:44.210269+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/r-internal-function-invocation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper does not describe any workflow or use case for retrieving assembly metadata before processing files. The two use cases presented (Analyzing Orbitrap Spectra and iRT Regression) both involve reading actual raw data files using exported functions, not querying internal assembly metadata.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "r-internal-function-invocation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
