    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/retention-time-extraction-from-raw-spectra/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The original purpose of these injections is automated longitudinal system suitability monitoring and quality control... This example shows how easy it is to perform iRT regression in R by just using the raw measurement data, our package rawrr... The fitted model can then be inspected using standard procedures. Figure 6 shows a visual inspection by plotting observed RTs as a function of iRT score together with the fitted model regression line.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates iRT-based RT extraction, linearity validation via regression, and system suitability/QC monitoring\u2014all use cases named in the card.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "retention-time-extraction-from-raw-spectra",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have Thermo Orbitrap .raw files containing known reference peptides (e.g., iRT standards) and need to (1) verify instrument retention time stability and linearity, (2) extract precise RT values at peak apex for calibration curves, or (3) validate LC-MS method performance",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:41:44.336298+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/retention-time-extraction-from-raw-spectra/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "rawrr utilizes a vendor-provided API named Raw File Reader to access spectral data logged in proprietary Thermo Fisher Scientific raw files... Our novel package rawrr now provides complete, OS-independent access to all spectral data logged in Thermo Fisher Scientific raw files.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms rawrr is Thermo-specific and mentions ProteoWizard and MSconvert (not ThermoRawFileParser) as conversion alternatives: 'Libraries that support working with the spectral data in R also exist, for instance, the Bioconductor package MSnbase. However, they require conversion of raw data to exchange formats like mzML, which is primarily supported by the Proteowizard project and its software tool MSconvert.' Card names ThermoRawFileParser but paper names MSconvert.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-0c00866",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "retention-time-extraction-from-raw-spectra",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Non-Thermo instruments (e.g., Bruker, AB Sciex, Waters Synapt): rawrr wraps RawFileReader, which reads only Thermo .raw files; alternative tools (ProteoWizard, ThermoRawFileParser) or formats (mzML, mzXML) are required.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:41:44.336298+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
