    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-quality-assurance-proteomics/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Use Case I: Analyzing Orbitrap Spectra... This use case shows how easy it is to work directly with raw-formated Orbitrap data after installing our R package rawrr which applies vendor APIs for data access... Figure 2 shows that all y-ion signals are several ten or even hundred folds above the noise estimate",
      "asbval:note": "Scope description matches the paper's Use Case I exactly: extracting scans, verifying instrument parameters (AGC, resolving power), and assessing S/N of fragment ions.",
